00:15:16,306 --> 00:15:20,885
Well, this fight you're havin' against
the Russian. Do you think maybe...

214
00:15:21,019 --> 00:15:23,060
it ain't against him?

215
00:15:23,773 --> 00:15:27,438
If it's not him, Stallion,
then who's it against?

216
00:15:27,569 --> 00:15:32,693
Well, do you think maybe it's, like...
you against you? What do you think?

217
00:15:32,824 --> 00:15:36,240
You know, I think you really
<i>are</i> gettin' brain-damaged.

218
00:15:36,369 --> 00:15:40,319
Maybe, but... really.
I'm speakin' the truth here, Apollo.

219
00:15:40,456 --> 00:15:43,126
- Are you?
- Yeah.

220
00:15:43,668 --> 00:15:49,124
- I don't think I wanna hear this, Stallion.
- Hey, Apollo, you were a great fighter,

221
00:15:49,257 --> 00:15:52,127
but, look, we gotta face the facts too.

222
00:15:52,260 --> 00:15:55,012
You don't wanna believe it,
but maybe the show is over.

223
00:15:55,138 --> 00:15:58,258
That's easy for you to say.
You're still on top.

224
00:15:58,391 --> 00:16:01,096
What happens when
you're not on top? Then what?

225
00:16:01,227 --> 00:16:04,976
Where do we go, Stallion?
Cos we sure as hell can't be born again.

226
00:16:05,106 --> 00:16:10,148
I know we can't be born again, but, let's
face it, we... we gotta change sometime.

227
00:16:10,278 --> 00:16:12,816
I don't wanna change! I like who I am!

228
00:16:12,947 --> 00:16:15,819
I like who you are, too, but look at that.

229
00:16:15,951 --> 00:16:18,738
That ain't us up there no more, Apollo.

230
00:16:18,871 --> 00:16:21,741
We can't do that the way we did it before.

231
00:16:21,874 --> 00:16:25,574
We're changin'. We're, like,
turnin' into regular people.

232
00:16:25,711 --> 00:16:28,914
No, Stallion!
Maybe you <i>think</i> you're changin'.

233
00:16:29,048 --> 00:16:34,290
But you can't change what you really are.
You can forget all this money and stuff.

234
00:16:34,428 --> 00:16:36,468
Cos it don't change a thing.

235
00:16:36,597 --> 00:16:40,595
You and me, we don't even have a choice.

236
00:16:40,726 --> 00:16:46,266
We're born with a killer instinct that you
can't just turn off and on like some radio.

237
00:16:46,398 --> 00:16:50,230
We <i>have</i> to be right in the middle of
the action, cos we're the warriors.

238
00:16:50,361 --> 00:16:53,148
Without some challenge,
some damn war to fight,

239
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:56,780
then the warrior may
as well be dead, Stallion.

240
00:16:59,954 --> 00:17:01,993
So I'm askin' you,

241
00:17:03,249 --> 00:17:05,288
as a friend,

242
00:17:08,712 --> 00:17:11,917
stand by my side this one last time.

243
00:17:14,886 --> 00:17:17,342
You're a great talker, Apollo.

244
00:17:19,975 --> 00:17:23,178
All right, but... when this is over?

245
00:17:26,356 --> 00:17:28,514
You know me, Stallion.

246
00:17:28,650 --> 00:17:31,106
I always think of somethin' else.

247
00:17:31,444 --> 00:17:35,656
That's what I'm afraid of.
All right. You got a deal there.

248
00:17:35,782 --> 00:17:38,487
I feel sorry for that guy, you know?

249
00:17:39,202 --> 00:17:42,820
What made you decide to put on
an exhibition fight with Drago?

250
00:17:42,956 --> 00:17:45,743
Let's call it a sense of responsibility.

251
00:17:45,875 --> 00:17:47,915
Responsibility, how?

252
00:17:48,044 --> 00:17:51,544
I had to teach this young fella
to box - American style!

253
00:17:51,673 --> 00:17:54,709
Isn't Drago a little inexperienced
to be in the same ring?

254
00:17:54,843 --> 00:17:58,461
Well, you know, some folks
got to learn the hard way!

255
00:17:59,723 --> 00:18:03,342
- No quick knockout predictions?
- No. I'm not angry with him.

256
00:18:03,477 --> 00:18:08,305
I just wanna show the whole world that
Russia doesn't have all the best athletes.

257
00:18:08,441 --> 00:18:11,774
Rocky, how do you think
Apollo should fight Drago?

258
00:18:11,903 --> 00:18:17,324
Well, personally, I think the first thing
you'd better get Apollo is a ladder.

259
00:18:18,284 --> 00:18:22,910
Drago, how does it feel to spar
with the great former champion?

260
00:18:24,332 --> 00:18:28,164
The man's tongue didn't
come through customs.

261
00:18:29,545 --> 00:18:32,214
My husband is very happy
to have this opportunity.

262
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:35,127
- It's his dream.
- Dream? How do you mean?

263
00:18:35,259 --> 00:18:39,304
In our country, Apollo Creed is
well known and very respected.

264
00:18:39,430 --> 00:18:44,009
- It could be a good victory.
- Whoa! Wait a minute, now. Hold it.

265
00:18:44,143 --> 00:18:49,101
When? Now you don't really think
you're gonna whip me, do ya?

266
00:18:49,232 --> 00:18:53,099
- Well, he didn't come here to lose.
- You hold on, little lady.

267
00:18:53,236 --> 00:18:56,818
- Lose, and lose royally, he's gonna do.
- How can you be so sure?

268
00:18:56,948 --> 00:19:02,239
I've been with the best. I beat the best.
I retired more men than Social Security!

269
00:19:02,371 --> 00:19:06,203
Excuse, please. You are not
very realistic, are you, Mr Creed?

270
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,326
What are <i>you</i> talkin' about?

271
00:19:08,460 --> 00:19:12,327
You can box, yes, but you are far too
old to think you can win over Drago.

272
00:19:12,464 --> 00:19:15,798
- Is that a fact?
- Yes! And it could be a painful one!

273
00:19:15,926 --> 00:19:19,509
Put that heavy bag with eyeballs
in the ring with me and <i>you'll</i> see pain!

274
00:19:19,638 --> 00:19:22,674
- Why do you insult us?
- Now you just hold on here.

275
00:19:22,808 --> 00:19:26,473
I'm not the bad guy. I came to talk
about a friendly exhibition bout

276
00:19:26,603 --> 00:19:30,601
- till Comrade Bigmouth started up!
- It is <i>you</i> who are the aggressor.

277
00:19:30,732 --> 00:19:33,567
I wish to say to the press, in all fairness,

278
00:19:33,694 --> 00:19:37,312
Drago should not even fight this man,
because he is a has-been.

279
00:19:37,447 --> 00:19:40,733
You get that big chump
in the ring right now...

280
00:19:44,204 --> 00:19:48,831
- Stop this before you get hurt.
- I don't wanna hear! Let that chump go!

281
00:19:51,796 --> 00:19:55,461
All right, all right. I've said what I feel.

282
00:19:55,592 --> 00:19:58,296
- We'll finish this in the ring!
- Wherever you like.

283
00:19:58,428 --> 00:20:03,255
You shut up, and all these puppets you
brought with you! You're history, chump!

284
00:20:03,391 --> 00:20:05,633
- How did I do?
- A little loud for me.

285
00:20:05,768 --> 00:20:07,927
- But good?
- Oh, yeah. Very good.

286
00:20:12,775 --> 00:20:16,026
<i>Welcome to the City of Lights -
<i>Las Vegas -

287
00:20:16,154 --> 00:20:20,198
<i>and to one of the most unusual</i>
<i>events in years... East meets West.</i>

288
00:20:20,617 --> 00:20:24,116
<i>Age versus youth in</i>
<i>a goodwill exhibition match,</i>

289
00:20:24,245 --> 00:20:28,029
<i>as the former champion Apollo Creed</i>
<i>takes on a mountain of muscle</i>

290
00:20:28,166 --> 00:20:31,250
<i>from the Soviet Union... Ivan Drago.</i>

291
00:20:31,377 --> 00:20:33,287
- Come on.
- Patience is a virtue.

292
00:20:33,421 --> 00:20:38,297
- I'm ready to rock 'n' roll.
- You gotta get your equipment.

293
00:20:38,426 --> 00:20:41,131
- Now you look like a mummy.
- I feel like a mummy.

294
00:20:41,262 --> 00:20:44,596
- How does it feel? OK?
- Feels great. I feel like I could eat nails.

295
00:20:44,724 --> 00:20:48,094
- I never tried them snails.
- What are you talkin' about?

296
00:20:48,228 --> 00:20:52,178
Snails. I never had 'em. I see 'em in
the garden, but I never want to eat 'em.

297
00:20:52,316 --> 00:20:57,856
I didn't say anythin' about snails.
I said nails. N-N-Nails, Stallion!

298
00:20:57,988 --> 00:21:00,823
You look pretty good, but, you know,

299
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:03,523
just do me a favour when you go up there.

300
00:21:03,661 --> 00:21:08,323
- Try not to wear yourself out, OK?
- Yeah, wear myself out. Sure.

301
00:21:08,457 --> 00:21:11,707
Well, it's just that you ain't
been in the ring for five years.

302
00:21:11,835 --> 00:21:16,747
- I just want you to... maintain a little bit.
- I'm in the best shape of my life.

303
00:21:16,882 --> 00:21:21,211
- I'm stronger, I'm quicker...
- Hey, I'm not sayin' you're not ready,

304
00:21:21,345 --> 00:21:23,966
but personally, if it were me,

305
00:21:24,098 --> 00:21:27,467
I wouldn't mind postponin'
a couple of weeks.

306
00:21:27,601 --> 00:21:29,558
Postpone?

307
00:21:29,687 --> 00:21:34,349
Come on, Apollo. We don't know anythin'
about this guy you're fightin', really.

308
00:21:34,483 --> 00:21:40,024
Let's say I postpone. I pull out, somebody
else steps in and whips this chump.

309
00:21:40,156 --> 00:21:44,071
- Then where does that leave me?
- This is just some kind of exhibition fight.

310
00:21:44,202 --> 00:21:47,986
- This thing don't mean nothin'.
- No, man. That's where you're wrong.

311
00:21:48,123 --> 00:21:51,408
This is <i>not</i> just an exhibition fight
that doesn't mean anything.

312
00:21:51,543 --> 00:21:56,288
This is us against them.
What are you talkin' about? Come on!

313
00:21:56,423 --> 00:21:58,462
Stallion...

314
00:21:58,592 --> 00:22:04,511
Maybe you don't know what I'm talkin'
about now, but you will when it's over.

315
00:22:06,474 --> 00:22:09,808
Believe me, you will when it's over.

316
00:22:19,571 --> 00:22:21,480
Ivan!

317
00:22:49,936 --> 00:22:53,102
Good luck. I hope after we can be friends.

318
00:22:53,606 --> 00:22:56,476
- I hope so.
- Of course. They're sportsmen,

319
00:22:56,609 --> 00:22:58,518
not soldiers.

320
00:23:01,530 --> 00:23:03,570
Enjoy the fight.

